1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,400
[customer] We saw duplicates in our transcript chunks. Could it be our uploader?

2
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:10,800
[agent] Possibly. Are retries sending the same chunk_id again without an idempotency key?

3
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:16,200
[customer] Yes — if the request times out we retry immediately with the same payload.

4
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:22,200
[agent] That explains it. Add an idempotency key per chunk and dedupe on ingest.

5
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:27,500
[customer] Makes sense. We’ll implement that and rerun our load test.

